♪ Gently Johnny, my jingle-o

265
00:21:03,629 --> 00:21:08,830
♪ Gently, gently, gently, Johnny

266
00:21:09,429 --> 00:21:15,141
♪ Gently Johnny, my jingle-o... ♪

267
00:21:20,830 --> 00:21:22,946
[woman giggles]

268
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:27,581
I think I could turn
and live with animals.

269
00:21:27,708 --> 00:21:30,828
They are so placid and self-contained.

270
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:35,943
They do not lie awake in the dark
and weep for their sins.

271
00:21:36,070 --> 00:21:40,780
They do not make me sick,
discussing their duty to God.

272
00:21:41,510 --> 00:21:43,820
Not one of them kneels to another,

273
00:21:43,949 --> 00:21:47,181
or to his own kind
that lived thousands of years ago.

274
00:21:48,708 --> 00:21:52,943
Not one of them is 'respectable'...

275
00:21:53,070 --> 00:21:55,708
or 'unhappy'...

276
00:21:55,830 --> 00:21:57,148
all over the earth.

277
00:21:57,270 --> 00:22:03,300
♪ Gently Johnny, my jingle-o

278
00:22:03,429 --> 00:22:09,108
♪ Gently, gently, gently, Johnny

279
00:22:09,228 --> 00:22:13,188
♪ Gently Johnny, my jingle-o... ♪

280
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:25,905
[woman groaning with pleasure]

281
00:22:53,030 --> 00:22:55,179
[cheering and shouting]

282
00:23:01,629 --> 00:23:03,780
[cockerel crows]

283
00:23:06,708 --> 00:23:08,542
Good morning, Sergeant.

284
00:23:08,669 --> 00:23:11,660
- Morning.
- Isn't it glorious?

285
00:23:11,790 --> 00:23:13,906
Aye, aye, it's very nice.

286
00:23:14,030 --> 00:23:16,543
I expect you'll be going home tonight?

287
00:23:17,869 --> 00:23:20,622
Well, that depends.

288
00:23:21,949 --> 00:23:23,986
Where's the school, please?

289
00:23:24,110 --> 00:23:26,419
On the far side of the green.

290
00:23:26,550 --> 00:23:28,666
Thank you.

291
00:23:32,629 --> 00:23:34,109
[♪ jew's harp]

292
00:23:43,990 --> 00:23:47,108
♪ In the woods there grew a tree

293
00:23:47,228 --> 00:23:50,744
♪ And a fine, fine tree was he

294
00:23:51,708 --> 00:23:55,385
♪ And on that tree there was a limb
And on that limb there was a branch

295
00:23:55,510 --> 00:23:59,025
♪ And on that branch there was a nest
And in that nest there was an egg

296
00:23:59,629 --> 00:24:02,939
♪ And in that egg there was a bird
And from that bird a feather came

297
00:24:03,110 --> 00:24:06,626
♪ And of that feather was...

298
00:24:06,750 --> 00:24:09,218
♪ Abed

299
00:24:16,350 --> 00:24:20,139
♪ And on that bed there was a girl
And on that girl there was a man

300
00:24:20,270 --> 00:24:24,023
♪ And from that man there was a seed
And from that seed there was a boy

301
00:24:24,148 --> 00:24:27,905
♪ And from that boy there was a man
