00:24:39,228 --> 00:24:41,266
♪ In Summerisle, Summerisle,
Summerisle, Summerisle

305
00:24:41,389 --> 00:24:45,064
♪ And on that bed there was a girl
And on that girl there was a man

306
00:24:45,189 --> 00:24:49,023
♪ And from that man there was a seed
And from that seed there was a boy

307
00:24:49,148 --> 00:24:52,780
♪ And from that boy there was a man
And for that man there was a grave

308
00:24:52,949 --> 00:24:56,500
♪ And from that grave there grew...

309
00:24:56,629 --> 00:24:59,099
♪ A tree

310
00:25:03,990 --> 00:25:05,946
♪ In Summerisle, Summerisle,
Summerisle, Summerisle

311
00:25:06,070 --> 00:25:10,506
♪ And on that tree there was a limb
And on that limb there was a branch...

312
00:25:13,629 --> 00:25:17,339
♪ ...and in that egg there was a bird,
And from that bird, a feather came

313
00:25:17,468 --> 00:25:20,781
♪ And of that feather was...

314
00:25:20,908 --> 00:25:23,629
♪ A bed... ♪

315
00:25:25,310 --> 00:25:30,100
Very well, girls. That's enough.
Now it's time to pay attention to me.

316
00:25:30,830 --> 00:25:32,467
Now, uh, Daisy,

317
00:25:32,590 --> 00:25:37,061
will you tell us what it is, please,
that the Maypole represents?

318
00:25:41,110 --> 00:25:43,021
[sighs heavily]

319
00:25:44,148 --> 00:25:46,744
Really, Daisy.
You've been told often enough.

320
00:25:46,869 --> 00:25:49,543
- Miss Rose, I know!
- I know!

321
00:25:49,669 --> 00:25:52,310
- All right, then, anybody.
- [all] Phallic symbol.

322
00:25:52,468 --> 00:25:56,508
[Rose] The phallic symbol.
That is correct.

323
00:25:56,629 --> 00:25:58,906
It is the image of the penis,

324
00:25:59,030 --> 00:26:02,181
which is venerated in religions
such as ours

325
00:26:02,310 --> 00:26:05,699
as symbolising
the generative force in nature.

326
00:26:07,790 --> 00:26:10,020
Oh, can I help you?

327
00:26:11,510 --> 00:26:14,070
C- could I have a word with you,
please, Miss?

328
00:26:14,189 --> 00:26:18,342
Certainly. Girls, open your desks
and take out your exercise books.

329
00:26:22,830 --> 00:26:26,026
Miss, you can be quite sure that I shall
report this to the proper authorities.

330
00:26:26,148 --> 00:26:28,664
Everywhere I go on this island,
it seems to me I find degeneracy.

331
00:26:28,790 --> 00:26:33,181
And there is brawling in bars,
there is indecency in public places,

332
00:26:33,310 --> 00:26:36,223
and there is corruption of the young,
and now I see it all stems from here.

333
00:26:36,389 --> 00:26:38,744
It stems from the filth taught here
in this very schoolroom.

334
00:26:38,869 --> 00:26:42,987
I was unaware that the police had
any authority in matters of education.

335
00:26:43,110 --> 00:26:46,580
Aye, aye, well,
we'll see about that.

336
00:26:46,708 --> 00:26:50,385
Girls, could I have your attention,
please?

337
00:26:52,350 --> 00:26:55,183
Now, I am a police officer.

338
00:26:56,510 --> 00:26:58,545
Well, as you can see.

339
00:26:58,669 --> 00:27:01,059
I have come here from the mainland

340
00:27:01,189 --> 00:27:04,945
to investigate
the disappearance of a young girl.

341
00:27:05,070 --> 00:27:07,664
I have a photograph here...
Excuse me.

342
00:27:07,790 --> 00:27:12,023
...which I would like you
to pass around amongst yourselves.

343
00:27:12,148 --> 00:27:15,984
Meanwhile, I'll write her name over there
on the blackboard.

344
00:27:32,030 --> 00:27:34,067
Rowan Morrison.

345
00:27:35,510 --> 00:27:37,466
That's her name.

346
00:27:38,550 --> 00:27:42,179
Now, do any of you recognise
either the name or the photograph?

347
00:27:42,310 --> 00:27:44,949
- No.
- There's your answer, Sergeant.

348
00:27:45,070 --> 00:27:48,266
If she existed, we would know her.

349
00:27:48,389 --> 00:27:52,270
- Whose desk is that?
- No one's.

350
00:27:55,550 --> 00:27:56,984
Thank you.

351
00:28:02,629 --> 00:28:04,744
[girls giggle]

352
00:28:06,228 --> 00:28:10,144
The little old beetle goes round and
round, always the same way, you see,

353
00:28:10,270 --> 00:28:14,309
till he ends up right up tight
to the nail, poor old thing.

354
00:28:14,429 --> 00:28:17,023
[giggling]

355
00:28:17,148 --> 00:28:18,821
"Poor old thing"?

356
00:28:18,990 --> 00:28:22,619
Then why in God's name
do you do it, girl?

357
00:28:24,389 --> 00:28:26,188
I'd like to see the school register,
please.

358
00:28:26,310 --> 00:28:28,949
I'm afraid you'll have to have
Lord Summerisle's authority.

359
00:28:29,070 --> 00:28:30,821
This is a police matter.

360
00:28:30,949 --> 00:28:33,179
I'm afraid you'll have to have
a search warrant or permission

361
00:28:33,310 --> 00:28:35,823
from Lord Summerisle himself.

362
00:28:35,949 --> 00:28:38,987
I'm afraid you'll just have
to bear with me, won't you?

363
00:28:56,030 --> 00:28:58,385
[Miss Rose clears her throat]

364
00:28:58,510 --> 00:29:02,185
You're liars.
You are despicable little liars.

365
00:29:02,310 --> 00:29:06,189
Rowan Morrison is
a schoolmate of yours, isn't she?

366
00:29:07,468 --> 00:29:09,824
And that is her desk, isn't it?

367
00:29:11,189 --> 00:29:12,510
- Well, isn't it?
- I think you ought to know...

368
00:29:12,669 --> 00:29:15,139
And you are the biggest liar of all!

369
00:29:16,350 --> 00:29:18,862
I warn you,
one more lie out of you,

370
00:29:20,310 --> 00:29:22,698
and I will charge you with obstruction.

371
00:29:22,830 --> 00:29:25,663
And, believe me, Miss Rose,
that is a promise.

372
00:29:28,869 --> 00:29:30,349
Now...

373
00:29:31,429 --> 00:29:33,262
...for the last time,

374
00:29:33,389 --> 00:29:36,109
where is Rowan Morrison?

375
00:29:36,228 --> 00:29:38,301
I would like to speak
to you outside, Sergeant.

376
00:29:38,429 --> 00:29:40,580
Girls, get on with your reading.

377
00:29:40,708 --> 00:29:45,306
It's the "Rites and Rituals of May Day",
chapter five. I won't be long.

378
00:29:48,590 --> 00:29:50,148
Well?

379
00:29:51,510 --> 00:29:56,583
You don't understand, Sergeant.
Nobody was lying. I told you plainly.

380
00:29:56,708 --> 00:29:59,907
If Rowan Morrison existed,
we would know of her.

381
00:30:00,030 --> 00:30:03,500
You mean, she doesn't exist?
She's dead?

382
00:30:05,708 --> 00:30:07,746
- You would say so.
- Oh, come on, come on.

383
00:30:07,869 --> 00:30:10,464
She's either dead, or she's not dead.

384
00:30:10,590 --> 00:30:13,785
Here, we do not use the word...

385
00:30:13,908 --> 00:30:16,468
[mouths "dead"]

386
00:30:16,590 --> 00:30:20,982
We believe that
when the human life is over,

387
00:30:21,110 --> 00:30:24,990
the soul returns to trees, to air,

388
00:30:25,110 --> 00:30:28,148
to fire, to water, to animals.

389
00:30:29,790 --> 00:30:32,622
So that Rowan Morrison
has simply returned

390
00:30:32,790 --> 00:30:35,258
to the life forces in another form.

391
00:30:35,389 --> 00:30:39,622
Do you mean to say
you teach the children this stuff?

392
00:30:39,750 --> 00:30:44,949
Yes. I told you,
it is what we believe.

393
00:30:45,070 --> 00:30:47,504
They never learn anything
of Christianity?

394
00:30:47,629 --> 00:30:50,302
Only as a comparative religion.

395
00:30:50,429 --> 00:30:53,309
The children find it
far easier to picture

396
00:30:53,429 --> 00:30:56,309
reincarnation than resurrection.

397
00:30:57,790 --> 00:31:00,828
Those rotting bodies
are a great stumbling block

398
00:31:00,949 --> 00:31:03,622
for the childish imagination.

399
00:31:03,750 --> 00:31:05,228
Why, of course.

400
00:31:05,350 --> 00:31:07,181
And may I ask,

401
00:31:07,310 --> 00:31:10,266
where is the rotting body
of Rowan Morrison?

402
00:31:10,389 --> 00:31:13,542
Right where you'd expect it to be,
in the earth.

403
00:31:14,830 --> 00:31:17,139
You mean, in the churchyard?

404
00:31:17,270 --> 00:31:21,059
- In a manner of speaking...
- No! In plain speaking.

405
00:31:22,429 --> 00:31:25,978
The building attached to the ground
in which the body lies

406
00:31:26,110 --> 00:31:29,262
is no longer used
for Christian worship,

407
00:31:29,429 --> 00:31:33,389
so whether it is still a churchyard
is debatable.

408
00:31:35,270 --> 00:31:39,423
But forgive me. I must get back
to my girls. Good morning to you.

409
00:32:00,790 --> 00:32:03,622
[Howie] "Here lieth Beech Buchanan,

410
00:32:03,750 --> 00:32:07,708
"protected by
the ejaculation of serpents"?

411
00:33:14,869 --> 00:33:18,181
- [Howie] Morning.
- Morning.

412
00:33:18,310 --> 00:33:21,188
I see you plant trees
on most of the graves here.

413
00:33:21,310 --> 00:33:24,824
- Aye, that's right.
- What tree is that?

414
00:33:24,949 --> 00:33:27,146
That's a rowan.

415
00:33:27,270 --> 00:33:29,737
- And who lies there?
- Rowan Morrison.

416
00:33:34,350 --> 00:33:37,545
- How long has she been dead?
- Oh, six or seven months.

417
00:33:37,669 --> 00:33:41,061
They're just a wee bit late
with the headstone.

418
00:33:41,228 --> 00:33:43,458
What on earth's that?
It looks like a piece of skin.

419
00:33:43,590 --> 00:33:46,706
- Why, so it is.
- Well, what is it?

420
00:33:47,869 --> 00:33:51,147
The poor wee lassie's navel string,
of course.

421
00:33:51,270 --> 00:33:55,581
Where else should it be
but hung on her own little tree?

422
00:33:56,908 --> 00:33:59,218
Where does your minister live?

423
00:33:59,350 --> 00:34:00,908
Minister?

424
00:34:01,030 --> 00:34:02,828
[chuckles]

425
00:34:07,590 --> 00:34:09,226
"Minister"!

426
00:34:13,589 --> 00:34:18,187
[May] What a silly girl you are to make
all this fuss. It's just a little frog.

427
00:34:18,350 --> 00:34:21,627
It'll do that poor sore throat good.

428
00:34:21,748 --> 00:34:23,741
Anyone'd think you didn't
want to get better.

429
00:34:23,870 --> 00:34:26,339
Now, in he goes!

430
00:34:31,029 --> 00:34:35,627
And out he comes. There.
Now, that didn't hurt much, did it?

431
00:34:35,748 --> 00:34:38,821
- [Myrtle] it tasted horrid.
- Never mind, darling. It's all over now.

432
00:34:38,949 --> 00:34:42,418
Here's your sweet for being a brave girl.
Which one would you like?

433
00:34:42,549 --> 00:34:47,828
There. He's got your horrid old sore
throat now, hasn't he, poor creature?

434
00:34:47,949 --> 00:34:49,906
Can't you hear him croaking?

435
00:34:51,069 --> 00:34:53,504
Can I do anything for you, Sergeant?

436
00:34:53,629 --> 00:34:57,225
I doubt it,
seeing you're all raving mad.

437
00:35:14,709 --> 00:35:16,587
Good day.

438
00:35:16,709 --> 00:35:19,542
I'd like to see
your index of deaths, please.

439
00:35:19,669 --> 00:35:21,707
Do you have authority?

440
00:35:25,790 --> 00:35:28,178
No, I meant from his lordship.

441
00:35:28,310 --> 00:35:29,504
I don't need it.

442
00:35:29,669 --> 00:35:33,345
I'm afraid you have to get permission
from Lord Summerisle.

443
00:35:34,509 --> 00:35:36,580
Miss...

444
00:35:36,709 --> 00:35:39,906
If you don't cooperate with me
here and now,

445
00:35:40,029 --> 00:35:43,988
you may well find yourself inside
a police cell on the mainland tonight!

446
00:35:44,109 --> 00:35:45,908
Have I made myself quite clear?

447
00:35:47,870 --> 00:35:49,747
Please.

448
00:35:57,749 --> 00:35:59,343
Thank you.

449
00:36:00,310 --> 00:36:02,620
M, M, M, M...

450
00:36:03,950 --> 00:36:06,703
"Benjamin and Rachel Morrison."

451
00:36:06,830 --> 00:36:08,901
Rachel and Benjamin...

452
00:36:10,310 --> 00:36:13,939
- Names from the Bible.
- Yes. They were very old.

453
00:36:15,790 --> 00:36:19,259
But there's no record
of Rowan Morrison's death,

454
00:36:19,430 --> 00:36:22,548
which means, of course,
there is no death certificate.

455
00:36:25,669 --> 00:36:28,787
- Did you know her?
- Yes, of course.

456
00:36:32,870 --> 00:36:35,544
- Is that her?
- Yes, that's her.

457
00:36:37,109 --> 00:36:39,499
How did she die?

458
00:36:41,629 --> 00:36:46,419
I don't know. I don't know
anything about her. Nothing.

459
00:36:53,350 --> 00:36:54,669
Thank you.

460
00:36:56,109 --> 00:36:58,544
[doorbell tinkles]

461
00:37:01,549 --> 00:37:03,859
[Howie] Are you Mr Lennox,
the photographer?

462
00:37:03,990 --> 00:37:07,984
Oh, I'm firstly a chemist,
secondly a photographer.

463
00:37:08,109 --> 00:37:10,942
I understand you take the harvest
festival photographs every year.

464
00:37:11,069 --> 00:37:13,663
- The ones I saw in The Green Man.
- Yes.

465
00:37:13,790 --> 00:37:15,781
It's rather humdrum work, I'm afraid.

466
00:37:15,910 --> 00:37:18,265
What happened
to last year's photograph?

467
00:37:18,390 --> 00:37:20,506
Isn't it there with the others?

468
00:37:20,629 --> 00:37:23,986
No, no, it's not. Apparently it's been
broken or damaged in some way.

469
00:37:24,109 --> 00:37:28,104
- Oh, what a pity.
- Would you have a copy of it?

470
00:37:28,229 --> 00:37:31,109
Oh, no, I don't keep copies.

471
00:37:31,229 --> 00:37:35,428
Mr Lennox, you were among the people
to whom I showed the photograph

472
00:37:35,589 --> 00:37:37,740
in the Green Man.

473
00:37:37,870 --> 00:37:40,339
Is that the girl?

474
00:37:40,509 --> 00:37:43,821
- [Lennox] It's difficult to say.
- Oh, come on, man!

475
00:37:43,950 --> 00:37:48,785
It was only eight months ago. Surely
you remember if it was that girl or not.

476
00:37:51,189 --> 00:37:52,589
Thank you.

477
00:37:54,149 --> 00:37:56,538
♪ Corn rigs and barley rigs

478
00:37:56,669 --> 00:38:00,788
♪ And corn rigs are bonnie

479
00:38:02,549 --> 00:38:06,020
