488
00:39:27,189 --> 00:39:34,142
♪ Fire seed and fire feed
and make the baby cry

489
00:39:34,270 --> 00:39:38,104
♪ Take the flame inside you
Burn and burn begin... ♪

490
00:39:40,310 --> 00:39:42,984
- His lordship is expecting you, sir.
- Expecting me?

491
00:39:43,109 --> 00:39:46,899
That's what his lordship told me, sir.
Would you please come this way?

492
00:39:48,549 --> 00:39:50,109
In there, sir.

493
00:40:08,910 --> 00:40:11,185
[clock chimes]

494
00:40:33,310 --> 00:40:35,665
Good afternoon, Sergeant Howie.

495
00:40:36,790 --> 00:40:39,828
I trust the sight of the young people
refreshes you.

496
00:40:39,950 --> 00:40:43,180
No, sir, it does not refresh me.

497
00:40:43,310 --> 00:40:45,267
Oh, I'm sorry.

498
00:40:45,390 --> 00:40:48,620
One should always be open
to the regenerative influences.

499
00:40:49,990 --> 00:40:52,629
I understand you're looking
for a missing girl.

500
00:40:52,749 --> 00:40:54,627
- I've found her.
- Splendid.

501
00:40:54,790 --> 00:40:58,305
In her grave. Your lordship is
a justice of the peace.

502
00:40:58,430 --> 00:41:00,227
I need your permission
to exhume her body,

503
00:41:00,350 --> 00:41:02,625
have it transported to the mainland
for a pathologist's report.

504
00:41:02,749 --> 00:41:05,582
You suspect...foul play?

505
00:41:05,709 --> 00:41:08,622
I suspect murder
and conspiracy to murder.

506
00:41:08,749 --> 00:41:11,310
In that case, you must go ahead.

507
00:41:12,390 --> 00:41:15,189
Your lordship seems
strangely unconcerned.

508
00:41:15,350 --> 00:41:17,944
I'm confident your suspicions
are wrong, Sergeant.

509
00:41:18,069 --> 00:41:22,620
We don't commit murder up here.
We're a deeply religious people.

510
00:41:23,390 --> 00:41:24,584
Religious?

511
00:41:24,709 --> 00:41:28,464
With ruined churches,
no ministers, no priests,

512
00:41:28,589 --> 00:41:30,819
and children dancing naked!

513
00:41:34,270 --> 00:41:36,658
[♪ plays notes on piano]

514
00:41:38,390 --> 00:41:40,381
[Lord] They do love
their divinity lessons.

515
00:41:40,509 --> 00:41:44,026
But th- they are...are naked.

516
00:41:44,149 --> 00:41:45,823
Naturally. It's much too dangerous

517
00:41:45,950 --> 00:41:48,863
to jump through the fire
with your clothes on.

518
00:41:49,950 --> 00:41:53,658
Wh- what religion c- c- can
they possibly be learning,

519
00:41:53,790 --> 00:41:55,939
jumping over bonfires?

520
00:41:56,069 --> 00:41:57,743
Parthenogenesis.

521
00:41:59,069 --> 00:42:00,390
What?

522
00:42:01,629 --> 00:42:05,988
Literally, as Miss Rose would
doubtless say in her assiduous way,

523
00:42:06,149 --> 00:42:09,301
reproduction without sexual union.

524
00:42:09,430 --> 00:42:11,705
Oh, what is all this?

525
00:42:11,830 --> 00:42:16,107
I mean, y- y- you've got
f- f- fake biology, fake religion.

526
00:42:16,229 --> 00:42:19,381
Sir, have these children
never heard of Jesus?

527
00:42:20,870 --> 00:42:26,582
Himself the son of a virgin,
impregnated, I believe, by a ghost.

528
00:42:28,270 --> 00:42:29,988
Do sit down, Sergeant.

529
00:42:30,109 --> 00:42:34,263
Shocks are so much better absorbed
with the knees bent.

530
00:42:34,430 --> 00:42:35,749
Please.

531
00:42:39,790 --> 00:42:42,225
Now, those children out there,

532
00:42:42,350 --> 00:42:44,625
they're jumping through the flames

533
00:42:44,749 --> 00:42:47,662
in the hope that the god of fire
will make them fruitful.

534
00:42:47,790 --> 00:42:49,622
Really, you can hardly blame them.

535
00:42:49,749 --> 00:42:52,263
After all, what girl would not prefer
the child of a god

536
00:42:52,390 --> 00:42:55,667
to that of some acne-scarred artisan?

537
00:42:55,790 --> 00:42:58,464
- And you encourage them in this?
- Actively.

538
00:42:58,589 --> 00:43:01,308
It's most important that each
new generation born on Summerisle

539
00:43:01,430 --> 00:43:04,660
be made aware that
here the old gods aren't dead.

540
00:43:04,790 --> 00:43:06,906
But what of the true god

541
00:43:07,029 --> 00:43:09,145
to whose glory churches
and monasteries have been built

542
00:43:09,270 --> 00:43:11,658
on these islands for generations past?

543
00:43:11,790 --> 00:43:13,939
Now, sir, what of him?

544
00:43:14,069 --> 00:43:17,107
He's dead. He can't complain.

545
00:43:17,229 --> 00:43:21,019
He had his chance,
and in the modern parlance, he blew it.

546
00:43:27,029 --> 00:43:31,307
- What?
- It's very simple. Let me show you.

547
00:43:31,430 --> 00:43:34,785
In the last century,
the islanders were starving.

548
00:43:34,950 --> 00:43:37,703
Like our neighbours today,
they were scratching a bare subsistence

549
00:43:37,870 --> 00:43:41,180
from sheep and sea.

550
00:43:41,310 --> 00:43:46,464
Then in 1868, my grandfather
bought this barren island

551
00:43:46,589 --> 00:43:48,740
and began to change things.

552
00:43:48,870 --> 00:43:53,022
A distinguished Victorian scientist,
agronomist, free thinker.

553
00:43:54,950 --> 00:43:57,863
How formidably benevolent he seems.

554
00:43:57,990 --> 00:44:02,109
Essentially the face of a man
incredulous of all human good.

555
00:44:02,229 --> 00:44:04,618
You're very cynical, my lord.

556
00:44:05,589 --> 00:44:07,705
What attracted my grandfather
to the island,

557
00:44:07,830 --> 00:44:11,823
apart from the profuse source
of wiry labour that it promised,

558
00:44:11,950 --> 00:44:14,703
was the unique combination
of volcanic soil

559
00:44:14,830 --> 00:44:17,743
and the warm Gulf Stream
that surrounded it.

560
00:44:17,910 --> 00:44:19,901
You see, his experiments
had led him to believe

561
00:44:20,029 --> 00:44:22,499
that it was possible to induce here
the successful growth

562
00:44:22,629 --> 00:44:25,542
of certain new strains of fruit
that he had developed.

563
00:44:25,669 --> 00:44:29,903
So, with typical mid-Victorian zeal,
he set to work.

564
00:44:30,029 --> 00:44:32,669
The best way of accomplishing this,
so it seemed to him,

565
00:44:32,790 --> 00:44:35,225
was to rouse the people
from their apathy

566
00:44:35,350 --> 00:44:38,421
by giving them back
their joyous old gods,

567
00:44:38,549 --> 00:44:40,381
and as a result of this worship,

568
00:44:40,509 --> 00:44:44,662
the barren island would burgeon
and bring forth fruit in great abundance.

569
00:44:44,790 --> 00:44:48,020
What he did, of course, was to develop
new cultivars of hardy fruits

570
00:44:48,189 --> 00:44:50,227
suited to local conditions.

571
00:44:50,350 --> 00:44:51,749
But, of course, to begin with,

572
00:44:51,870 --> 00:44:53,986
they worked for him
because he fed them and clothed them,

573
00:44:54,149 --> 00:44:58,064
but later, when the trees starting fruiting,
it became a very different matter.

574
00:44:58,189 --> 00:45:01,022
And the ministers fled the island,
never to return.

575
00:45:01,149 --> 00:45:03,868
What my grandfather
had started out of expediency,

576
00:45:03,990 --> 00:45:06,903
my father continued out of...love.

577
00:45:08,149 --> 00:45:10,187
He brought me up the same way,

578
00:45:10,310 --> 00:45:15,145
to reverence the music and the drama
and the rituals of the old gods.

579
00:45:16,310 --> 00:45:19,381
To love nature and to fear it,

580
00:45:20,629 --> 00:45:23,587
and to rely on it and to appease it
where necessary.

581
00:45:23,709 --> 00:45:27,020
- He brought me up...
- He brought you up to be a pagan!

582
00:45:28,629 --> 00:45:32,863
A heathen, conceivably,
but not, I hope, an unenlightened one.

583
00:45:34,990 --> 00:45:39,984
Lord Summerisle, I am interested
in one thing: the law.

584
00:45:40,109 --> 00:45:43,466
But I must remind you, sir,
that despite everything you've said,

585
00:45:43,589 --> 00:45:46,787
you are the subject
of a Christian country.

586
00:45:48,910 --> 00:45:54,667
Now, sir, if I may have your permission
to exhume the body of Rowan Morrison.

587
00:45:54,790 --> 00:45:57,781
I was under the impression
I'd already given it to you.

588
00:45:57,910 --> 00:45:59,981
Ah, there's your transport.

589
00:46:00,109 --> 00:46:03,421
It's been a great pleasure
meeting a Christian copper.

590
00:46:35,669 --> 00:46:38,662
[chuckles]

591
00:46:40,029 --> 00:46:41,941
[piano string breaks and whines]

592
00:46:43,669 --> 00:46:47,060
[woman] ♪ A maiden did
this tinker meet

593
00:46:47,189 --> 00:46:50,261
♪ And to him boldly say

594
00:46:50,390 --> 00:46:53,508
♪ "Oh, sure,
My kettle hath much need

595
00:46:53,629 --> 00:46:56,941
♪ "if you will pass my way"

596
00:46:57,109 --> 00:47:03,788
♪ She took the tinker by the hand
and led him to her door

597
00:47:03,950 --> 00:47:06,942
♪ Says she,
"My kettle I will show

598
00:47:07,069 --> 00:47:10,142
♪ "And you can clout it sure"

599
00:47:10,270 --> 00:47:15,709
♪ For patching and plugging
is his delight... ♪

600
00:47:19,229 --> 00:47:24,383
I found that
in Rowan Morrison's grave.

601
00:47:28,830 --> 00:47:31,821
Little Rowan loved the March hares.

602
00:47:31,950 --> 00:47:33,428
Hmm.

603
00:47:34,470 --> 00:47:35,823
It's sacrilege!

604
00:47:35,950 --> 00:47:41,183
Only if the ground is consecrated
to the Christian belief.

605
00:47:41,310 --> 00:47:46,305
Personally, I think it makes
a very lovely transmutation.

606
00:47:46,430 --> 00:47:50,343
I'm sure Rowan is most happy with it.
Do you not think so, Lord Summerisle?

607
00:47:50,470 --> 00:47:55,100
Miss, I hope you don't think that
I can be made a fool of indefinitely.

608
00:47:55,229 --> 00:47:57,506
Where is Rowan Morrison?

609
00:47:59,910 --> 00:48:03,107
Why, here she is,
what remains of her physically.

610
00:48:04,430 --> 00:48:06,261
Her soul, of course, may even now...

611
00:48:06,430 --> 00:48:08,625
Lord Summerisle!

612
00:48:08,749 --> 00:48:11,821
Where is Rowan Morrison?

613
00:48:13,669 --> 00:48:16,946
Sergeant Howie, I think that...

614
00:48:17,069 --> 00:48:21,109
you are supposed to be
the detective here.

615
00:48:27,189 --> 00:48:31,899
A child is reported missing
on your island.

616
00:48:34,149 --> 00:48:37,586
At first,
I'm told there is no such child.

617
00:48:37,749 --> 00:48:41,982
I then find that there is, in fact,
but that she has been killed.

618
00:48:42,109 --> 00:48:46,627
I subsequently discover that
there is no death certificate.

619
00:48:46,749 --> 00:48:49,901
And now I find
that there is a grave.

620
00:48:51,430 --> 00:48:53,500
There's no body.

621
00:48:55,870 --> 00:48:58,100
Very perplexing for you.

622
00:49:00,950 --> 00:49:03,544
What do you think could've happened?

623
00:49:05,950 --> 00:49:10,307
I think Rowan Morrison
was murdered

624
00:49:10,430 --> 00:49:14,310
under circumstances
of pagan barbarity,

625
00:49:14,430 --> 00:49:16,740
which I can scarcely bring
myself to believe

626
00:49:16,870 --> 00:49:19,544
as taking place in the 20th century.

627
00:49:21,310 --> 00:49:24,587
Now, it is my intention tomorrow
to return to the mainland

628
00:49:24,709 --> 00:49:27,178
and report my suspicions
to the Chief Constable

629
00:49:27,310 --> 00:49:29,984
of the West Highland constabulary.

630
00:49:30,109 --> 00:49:32,828
And I will demand
a full inquiry takes place

631
00:49:32,950 --> 00:49:36,102
into the affairs of this heathen island.

632
00:49:38,430 --> 00:49:41,104
You must, of course,
do as you see fit, Sergeant.

633
00:49:44,229 --> 00:49:47,028
Perhaps it's just as well that
you won't be here tomorrow,

634
00:49:47,149 --> 00:49:51,508
to be offended by the sight
of our May Day celebrations here.

635
00:49:55,430 --> 00:49:58,979
Broome, would you kindly
show the Sergeant out?

636
00:49:59,109 --> 00:50:01,147
- This way, sir.
- Goodbye.

637
00:50:02,310 --> 00:50:05,267
♪ Fair maid, says he,
your kettle's cracked

638
00:50:05,390 --> 00:50:08,269
♪ The cause is plainly told

639
00:50:08,390 --> 00:50:11,508
♪ There hath so many nails
been drove

640
00:50:11,629 --> 00:50:14,383
♪ Mine own could not take hold... ♪

641
00:51:22,509 --> 00:51:25,423
There's hardly any produce.

642
00:51:26,549 --> 00:51:28,904
Well, that's it, the crops failed.

643
00:51:30,350 --> 00:51:34,582
And it's Rowan.
Rowan and the crops failed!

644
00:51:35,790 --> 00:51:37,189
Sacrifice.

645
00:51:38,790 --> 00:51:41,669
[Summerisle] 'Perhaps it's just as well
that you won't be here

646
00:51:41,790 --> 00:51:45,908
'to be offended by the sight
of our May Day celebrations tomorrow.'

647
00:51:48,069 --> 00:51:50,379
[Willow] Sergeant?

648
00:51:55,149 --> 00:51:57,346
[rustling]

649
00:52:01,910 --> 00:52:03,901
[curtains drawn]

650
00:52:21,749 --> 00:52:23,979
♪ Mmm...

651
00:52:26,149 --> 00:52:30,109
♪ Heigh ho

652
00:52:31,350 --> 00:52:33,067
♪ Who is there?

653
00:52:37,390 --> 00:52:42,145
♪ No one but me my dear

654
00:52:44,270 --> 00:52:48,707
♪ Please come

655
00:52:49,470 --> 00:52:52,781
♪ Say how do

656
00:52:55,669 --> 00:53:02,906
♪ The things I'll give to you

657
00:53:03,029 --> 00:53:10,026
♪ A stroke as gentle as a feather

658
00:53:15,350 --> 00:53:20,026
♪ Heigh ho

659
00:53:20,149 --> 00:53:24,303
♪ I am here

660
00:53:27,069 --> 00:53:33,669
♪ Am I not young and fair?

661
00:53:33,790 --> 00:53:38,819
♪ Please come

662
00:53:38,950 --> 00:53:45,582
♪ Say how do

663
00:53:45,709 --> 00:53:51,388
♪ The things I'll show to you

664
00:53:52,830 --> 00:54:00,225
♪ Would you have a wondrous sight?

665
00:54:01,509 --> 00:54:07,346
♪ Mm-hm, the midday sun

666
00:54:09,350 --> 00:54:13,627
♪ At midnight

667
00:54:18,069 --> 00:54:23,303
♪ Fair maid

668
00:54:23,470 --> 00:54:27,747
♪ White and red

669
00:54:29,950 --> 00:54:36,299
♪ Comb you smooth
and stroke your head

670
00:54:37,109 --> 00:54:41,785
♪ Mm-hm... I

671
00:55:05,629 --> 00:55:07,779
[pounding grows more intense]

672
00:55:47,790 --> 00:55:50,781
[pounding gradually fades]

673
00:56:02,790 --> 00:56:05,020
Wake up, Sergeant.

674
00:56:09,069 --> 00:56:11,948
- What time is it?
- It's past nine.

675
00:56:15,990 --> 00:56:18,903
I thought you were gonna
come and see me last night.

676
00:56:20,870 --> 00:56:22,781
I invited you.

677
00:56:22,910 --> 00:56:24,901
I'm engaged to be married.

678
00:56:25,029 --> 00:56:27,669
[chuckles] Does that stop you?

679
00:56:31,350 --> 00:56:32,669
Ave. Aye.

680
00:56:32,790 --> 00:56:35,542
I must say,
you are a gallant fellow, Sergeant.

681
00:56:37,109 --> 00:56:38,986
It's nothing personal.

682
00:56:39,709 --> 00:56:41,747
Just that I don't believe in it.

683
00:56:42,790 --> 00:56:44,383
Before marriage.

684
00:56:44,509 --> 00:56:46,227
Suit yourself.

685
00:56:46,350 --> 00:56:48,990
I expect you'll be going back today.

686
00:56:49,109 --> 00:56:52,102
You don't want to be around here
on May Day.

687
00:56:52,229 --> 00:56:54,506
Not the way you feel.

688
00:57:02,950 --> 00:57:06,624
We carry death out of the village!

689
00:57:06,749 --> 00:57:10,299
We carry death
out of the village!

690
00:57:10,470 --> 00:57:14,428
We carry death out of the village!

691
00:57:14,549 --> 00:57:16,267
We carry death...

692
00:57:16,390 --> 00:57:19,667
[Howie] "'May Day festivals...

693
00:57:19,790 --> 00:57:22,908
"'Primitive man lived and died
by his harvest.

694
00:57:23,029 --> 00:57:27,024
"'The purpose of his spring ceremonies
was to ensure a plentiful autumn.

695
00:57:27,149 --> 00:57:31,144
"'Relics of these fertility dramas
are to be found all over Europe.

696
00:57:31,270 --> 00:57:33,738
"'In Great Britain, for example,
one can still see

697
00:57:33,910 --> 00:57:37,618
"'harmless versions of them danced
in obscure villages on May Day.

698
00:57:37,790 --> 00:57:40,747
"'Their cast includes
many alarming characters:

699
00:57:40,870 --> 00:57:42,986
"'a man-animal, or hobbyhorse,

700
00:57:43,109 --> 00:57:46,625
"'who canters at the head
of the procession, charging at the girls.

701
00:57:46,749 --> 00:57:48,979
"'A man-woman, the sinister teaser,

702
00:57:49,109 --> 00:57:51,464
"'played by the community leader
or priest.

703
00:57:51,589 --> 00:57:54,263
"'And a man-fool, Punch,

704
00:57:54,430 --> 00:57:57,343
"'most complex
of all the symbolic figures,

705
00:57:57,470 --> 00:58:01,303
"'the privileged simpleton
and king for a day.

706
00:58:01,430 --> 00:58:03,341
"'Six swordsmen follow these figures

707
00:58:03,470 --> 00:58:06,303
"'and at the climax of the ceremony
lock their swords together

708
00:58:06,430 --> 00:58:08,386
"'in a clear symbol of the Sun.

709
00:58:08,509 --> 00:58:12,468
"'In pagan times, however, these dances
were not simply picturesque jigs.

710
00:58:12,589 --> 00:58:15,058
"'They were frenzied rites
ending in a sacrifice

711
00:58:15,189 --> 00:58:17,147
"'by which the dancers
hoped desperately

712
00:58:17,270 --> 00:58:19,307
"'to win over the goddess of the fields.

713
00:58:19,430 --> 00:58:23,060
"'In good times, they offered produce
to the gods and slaughtered animals,

714
00:58:23,189 --> 00:58:26,341
"'but in bad years,
when the harvest had been poor...

715
00:58:27,350 --> 00:58:30,229
"'the sacrifice was a human being.

716
00:58:34,109 --> 00:58:36,147
'Rowan's not dead!'

717
00:58:37,509 --> 00:58:39,865
"Sometimes the victim
would be drowned in the sea

718
00:58:39,990 --> 00:58:43,620
"or burnt to death
in a huge sacrificial bonfire.

719
00:58:43,749 --> 00:58:48,620
"Sometimes the six swordsmen
ritually beheaded the virgin."

720
00:58:48,749 --> 00:58:53,142
Dear God in Heaven,
even these people can't be that mad.

721
00:58:55,109 --> 00:58:58,022
"The chief priest then
skinned the child,

722
00:58:58,149 --> 00:59:00,618
"and wearing the still-warmed skin
like a mantle,

723
00:59:00,790 --> 00:59:03,828
"led the rejoicing crowds
through the streets.

724
00:59:05,549 --> 00:59:08,827
"The priest thus represented
the goddess reborn

725
00:59:08,950 --> 00:59:12,544
"and guaranteed another
successful harvest next year."

726
00:59:13,270 --> 00:59:14,863
[sighs heavily]

727
00:59:21,589 --> 00:59:23,660
Good morning, Sergeant!

728
00:59:24,390 --> 00:59:25,982
I need to get to my plane.

729
00:59:26,149 --> 00:59:29,859
Oh, well, on May Day,
I'd better take you out myself.

730
00:59:35,910 --> 00:59:37,502
That's it.

731
00:59:39,830 --> 00:59:41,343
Here, right.

732
00:59:44,189 --> 00:59:47,182
[Howie] I shall be back shortly
with some more police officers.

733
01:00:19,109 --> 01:00:22,147
Have a good flight, then!

734
01:00:37,029 --> 01:00:39,544
Hey, you come back here!

735
01:00:41,990 --> 01:00:43,741
I said, come back here!

736
01:00:53,669 --> 01:00:55,899
What's the matter? Won't she go?

737
01:00:56,069 --> 01:00:59,187
No. Has anyone been here?

738
01:00:59,310 --> 01:01:01,267
Not to my knowledge, Sergeant.

739
01:01:01,390 --> 01:01:04,189
If any of the children had been
interfering with it,

740
01:01:04,310 --> 01:01:05,903
I'm sure I would've seen them.

741
01:01:06,029 --> 01:01:08,703
I warn you,
you're obstructing a police officer.

742
01:01:08,830 --> 01:01:12,299
I am not obstructing you, Sergeant.

743
01:01:12,430 --> 01:01:16,218
You could maybe get old Sam there
to row you to the mainland.

744
01:01:16,350 --> 01:01:18,785
You'd be back in a week.

745
01:01:18,910 --> 01:01:20,981
[cackles]

746
01:01:21,109 --> 01:01:26,263
Well, I'll just have to find
Rowan Morrison myself.

747
01:02:16,950 --> 01:02:19,100
[indistinct voices]

748
01:02:19,229 --> 01:02:21,301
[♪ traditional Scottish music]

749
01:02:33,430 --> 01:02:36,899
[children screaming and laughing]

750
01:02:38,350 --> 01:02:41,627
- Everything under control, Oak?
- Aye, my lord.

751
01:02:46,149 --> 01:02:47,220
Mr MacGreagor,

752
01:02:47,390 --> 01:02:50,428
I trust we aren't going to have
to let out your costume again this year.

753
01:02:50,549 --> 01:02:56,341
I think I'll manage, my lord, but it does
seem to shrink a little each year.

754
01:02:59,430 --> 01:03:01,580
[cymbals resound]

755
01:03:08,549 --> 01:03:10,540
[Summerisle]
My friends, enough now.

756
01:03:10,669 --> 01:03:15,790
We shall all reassemble
outside the town hall at 3:00 sharp,

757
01:03:15,910 --> 01:03:19,140
and then process through the village
and the countryside,

758
01:03:19,270 --> 01:03:21,499
down to the beach
below the stones,

759
01:03:21,629 --> 01:03:24,542
by the route which has become
sacred to our rite.

760
01:03:24,669 --> 01:03:28,549
This year at the procession's end,
as has already been proclaimed,

761
01:03:28,669 --> 01:03:32,549
a holy sacrifice will be offered up
jointly to Nuada,

762
01:03:32,669 --> 01:03:34,819
our most sacred god of the sun,

763
01:03:34,950 --> 01:03:38,466
and to Avellenau,
the beloved goddess of our orchards,

764
01:03:38,589 --> 01:03:42,823
in order that we may furnish them
with renewed power

765
01:03:42,990 --> 01:03:45,459
to quicken the growth of our crops.

766
01:03:45,589 --> 01:03:49,504
- Hail the Queen of the May!
- Hail the Queen of the May!

767
01:03:49,629 --> 01:03:52,270
Hail the Queen of the May!

768
01:03:54,709 --> 01:03:56,587
[doorbell tinkles]

769
01:03:58,310 --> 01:04:01,109
[May] Why, Sergeant,
I thought you'd gone back.

770
01:04:01,229 --> 01:04:05,303
Mrs Morrison, I don't know
if you know it or not,

771
01:04:05,470 --> 01:04:08,428
but Rowan is not dead,
they've got her hidden somewhere.

772
01:04:08,549 --> 01:04:10,028
They?

773
01:04:10,149 --> 01:04:13,939
If you know where she is, I beg you
to tell me now before it's too late.

774
01:04:14,069 --> 01:04:16,584
- Sergeant, I've already told you...
- In the name of God, woman!

775
01:04:16,709 --> 01:04:18,462
What kind of mother are you,

776
01:04:18,589 --> 01:04:20,627
that can stand by and see
your own child slaughtered?

777
01:04:20,749 --> 01:04:24,060
Sergeant, if I were you,
I would go back to the mainland.

778
01:04:24,189 --> 01:04:27,261
Stop interfering in things
that are no concern of yours.

779
01:04:27,390 --> 01:04:31,098
I am going to search every house
in this place during the next few hours,

780
01:04:31,229 --> 01:04:34,142
and if anybody, including you,
stands in my way,

781
01:04:34,270 --> 01:04:37,022
they'll be arrested
as accomplices to murder.

782
01:04:37,149 --> 01:04:41,109
You'll simply never understand
the true nature of sacrifice.

783
01:04:43,390 --> 01:04:45,381
Heathens! Bloody heathens!

784
01:04:47,270 --> 01:04:48,544
[rings doorbell]

785
01:04:48,669 --> 01:04:51,741
- Yes?
- [Howie] Take those masks off!

786
01:04:51,870 --> 01:04:54,020
- No.
- Take them off!

787
01:04:57,589 --> 01:04:59,421
- What do you think you're doing?
- Searching every house

788
01:04:59,549 --> 01:05:01,859
for a missing child.

789
01:05:29,189 --> 01:05:34,424
[woman] ♪ Baa-baa black sheep,
have you any wool?

790
01:05:34,549 --> 01:05:39,703
♪ Yes, sir, yes, sir,
three bags full

791
01:05:45,669 --> 01:05:47,263
I-I'm sorry.

792
01:06:01,549 --> 01:06:03,426
[giggles]

793
01:06:46,229 --> 01:06:48,665
- [Howie] What's that?
- The life of the fields.

794
01:06:49,749 --> 01:06:51,183
John Barleycorn.

795
01:06:51,310 --> 01:06:53,426
What's in here?

796
01:06:55,189 --> 01:06:57,261
- [Howie] What's that?
- That's my costume.

797
01:06:57,430 --> 01:06:59,705
The salmon of knowledge.

798
01:07:30,790 --> 01:07:32,861
[cheering and whooping]

799
01:07:42,470 --> 01:07:45,700
Hello. You're back early.

800
01:07:45,830 --> 01:07:48,343
Where are the other coppers?

801
01:07:48,470 --> 01:07:51,781
There aren't any.
The plane wouldn't start.

802
01:07:55,669 --> 01:07:57,627
Give me a glass of whiskey, please.

803
01:07:57,749 --> 01:08:01,868
So he spent his time instead
turning the whole village upside down.

804
01:08:01,990 --> 01:08:06,540
- Just give me a glass of whiskey!
- No wonder he's worn out.

805
01:08:06,709 --> 01:08:08,700
Did you find the girl?

806
01:08:09,749 --> 01:08:12,549
No, well, I can't say
I'm very surprised.

807
01:08:14,069 --> 01:08:16,505
I'm going to rest in my bed
for half an hour.

808
01:08:16,630 --> 01:08:18,778
I do not wish to be disturbed.

809
01:08:18,908 --> 01:08:21,627
I'd stay there until tonight,
if I was you!

810
01:08:21,750 --> 01:08:24,822
We don't much relish strangers
around today!

811
01:08:32,710 --> 01:08:35,304
[Willow] He's asleep.

812
01:08:35,429 --> 01:08:37,818
I don't like to use it on him, really.

813
01:08:37,988 --> 01:08:40,707
The laird said we're to take
no chances, didn't he?

814
01:08:40,868 --> 01:08:44,625
I know, but with the Hand of Glory
there's no telling when you wake.

815
01:08:44,788 --> 01:08:46,984
- He might sleep for days.
- All the better.

816
01:08:47,108 --> 01:08:48,384
Shh!

817
01:08:48,509 --> 01:08:52,264
We don't want him butting in.
Go on, light it up.

818
01:09:14,630 --> 01:09:18,099
That'll make you sleep,
my pretty Sergeant.

819
01:09:23,670 --> 01:09:27,377
I'm away to change.
We can't do without Punch.

820
01:09:29,108 --> 01:09:30,987
You best get on ahead.

821
01:09:31,108 --> 01:09:33,577
They've given you girls
five minutes start, haven't they?

822
01:09:33,710 --> 01:09:34,858
Goodbye.

823
01:09:57,228 --> 01:09:59,027
[MacGreagor groans]

824
01:10:18,830 --> 01:10:20,581
[excited laughter]

825
01:10:25,670 --> 01:10:28,469
[approaching drums]

826
01:10:31,389 --> 01:10:34,268
[♪ brass horns play]

827
01:10:53,589 --> 01:10:57,584
What's the matter with you,
MacGreagor? You call that dancing?

828
01:10:57,710 --> 01:11:00,987
Cut some capers, man.
Use your bladder!

829
01:11:01,108 --> 01:11:03,750
Play the fool.
That's what you're here for.

830
01:11:05,228 --> 01:11:08,425
I suppose you've been getting drunk
at your own bar.

831
01:11:47,790 --> 01:11:50,987
[women screaming and laughing]

832
01:12:06,830 --> 01:12:08,468
That's more like it!

833
01:12:09,990 --> 01:12:11,549
Good, good!

834
01:12:19,630 --> 01:12:22,063
[screaming and laughter]

835
01:12:31,750 --> 01:12:34,661
[steady drumbeat]

836
01:13:47,710 --> 01:13:51,907
[Summerisle] Chop!
[all] Chop! Chop! Chop!

837
01:13:52,029 --> 01:13:54,749
[chanting continues]

838
01:13:58,950 --> 01:14:02,465
Chop! Chop! Chop!

839
01:14:24,429 --> 01:14:27,023
[Summerisle] Everyone must go through,
MacGreagor.

840
01:14:27,148 --> 01:14:29,219
It's a game of chance, remember.

841
01:14:31,710 --> 01:14:34,621
[all] Chop! Chop! Chop!

842
01:14:50,309 --> 01:14:51,742
[chanting stops]

843
01:14:54,429 --> 01:14:55,907
[frightened screams]

844
01:15:04,790 --> 01:15:07,987
It's Holly. Well done!

845
01:15:08,108 --> 01:15:10,420
[man] It's wee Holly.

846
01:15:10,589 --> 01:15:12,818
[laughter and cheering]

847
01:15:12,950 --> 01:15:18,661
- Now, my friends, to the beach.
- [all] To the beach!

848
01:15:20,910 --> 01:15:23,469
[excited conversation
and laughter]

849
01:15:34,990 --> 01:15:40,303
O god of the sea,
I offer you this ale as a libation,

850
01:15:40,429 --> 01:15:44,866
that you may bestow upon us
in the year to come

851
01:15:44,990 --> 01:15:49,300
the rich and diverse fruits
of your kingdom.

852
01:15:53,910 --> 01:15:56,867
Hail, god of the seas!

853
01:15:56,990 --> 01:15:58,822
Accept our offering!

854
01:16:07,910 --> 01:16:12,425
And now,
for our more dreadful sacrifice

855
01:16:12,549 --> 01:16:15,701
for those who command
the fruit of the Earth.

856
01:16:15,830 --> 01:16:18,389
[horn blares]

857
01:16:23,990 --> 01:16:26,379
[Howie] It's Rowan.

858
01:16:33,228 --> 01:16:35,982
What's the matter, Mr MacGreagor?

859
01:16:36,108 --> 01:16:38,067
Now, don't be frightened.
I'm a police officer.

860
01:16:38,188 --> 01:16:40,782
- I've got to try and get you away.
- [Rowan] Hurry, please.

861
01:16:40,910 --> 01:16:44,540
I don't like it here. They're coming.
You know what they're going to do?

862
01:16:44,670 --> 01:16:48,026
[Howie] I know what they're going to do.
Come on, come on. Hurry, hurry!

863
01:16:51,389 --> 01:16:53,745
We can escape through the cave.
I know the way.

864
01:16:58,228 --> 01:16:59,664
Quickly.

865
01:17:14,228 --> 01:17:17,063
[Rowan] That's the way out, up there.

866
01:17:26,068 --> 01:17:29,505
Come on. It's through a big tunnel.

867
01:17:43,549 --> 01:17:45,904
We seem to have lost
our torch-bearing friends.

868
01:17:46,029 --> 01:17:48,464
I'm sorry. It was worse
than I remembered it.

869
01:18:02,509 --> 01:18:05,946
- Did I do it right?
- You did it beautifully.

870
01:18:06,068 --> 01:18:07,581
Dear little Rowan.

871
01:18:17,670 --> 01:18:20,549
Rowan, darling! Come on, now.

872
01:18:46,029 --> 01:18:47,666
Welcome, fool.

873
01:18:48,509 --> 01:18:52,389
You have come of your own free will
to the appointed place.

874
01:18:53,870 --> 01:18:55,986
The game's over.

875
01:18:56,148 --> 01:18:59,027
Game? What game?

876
01:18:59,148 --> 01:19:02,300
The game of the hunted
leading the hunter.

877
01:19:02,429 --> 01:19:05,343
You came here
to find Rowan Morrison,

878
01:19:05,469 --> 01:19:09,099
but it is we who have found you
and brought you here,

879
01:19:09,228 --> 01:19:13,108
and controlled your every thought
and action since you arrived.

880
01:19:14,509 --> 01:19:16,625
Principally,
we persuaded you to think

881
01:19:16,750 --> 01:19:19,389
that Rowan Morrison
was being held as a sacrifice

882
01:19:19,549 --> 01:19:22,188
because our crops failed last year.

883
01:19:22,309 --> 01:19:24,822
I know your crops failed.
I saw the harvest photograph.

884
01:19:24,950 --> 01:19:28,943
Oh, yes. They failed, all right.
Disastrously so.

885
01:19:29,068 --> 01:19:32,425
For the first time
since my grandfather came here.

886
01:19:33,630 --> 01:19:37,464
The blossom came, but the fruit
withered and died on the bough.

887
01:19:37,589 --> 01:19:41,661
That must not happen again this year.

888
01:19:41,790 --> 01:19:45,420
It is our most earnest belief that
the best way of preventing this

889
01:19:45,549 --> 01:19:49,066
is to offer to our god of the sun
and to the goddess of our orchards

890
01:19:49,188 --> 01:19:53,343
the most acceptable sacrifice
that lies in our power.

891
01:19:54,630 --> 01:19:58,224
Animals are fine,
but their acceptability is limited.

892
01:19:58,349 --> 01:20:02,344
A little child is even better,
but not nearly as effective

893
01:20:02,509 --> 01:20:04,978
as the right kind of adult.

894
01:20:06,589 --> 01:20:10,549
What do you mean,
"right kind of adult"?

895
01:20:14,750 --> 01:20:18,459
You, Sergeant,
are the right kind of adult,

896
01:20:18,589 --> 01:20:22,026
as our painstaking researches
have revealed.

897
01:20:22,148 --> 01:20:26,383
You, uniquely,
were the one we needed.

898
01:20:26,509 --> 01:20:28,705
A man who would come here
of his own free will.

899
01:20:28,870 --> 01:20:31,509
A man who has come here
with the power of a king

900
01:20:31,630 --> 01:20:33,621
by representing the law.

901
01:20:33,790 --> 01:20:36,224
A man who would come here
as a virgin.

902
01:20:36,349 --> 01:20:39,308
A man who has come here
as a fool.

903
01:20:41,309 --> 01:20:43,505
Get out of my way.

904
01:21:10,750 --> 01:21:13,103
You are the fool, Mr Howie.

905
01:21:13,228 --> 01:21:18,589
Punch, one of the great
fool-victims of history.

906
01:21:19,589 --> 01:21:23,947
For you have accepted
the role of king for a day,

907
01:21:24,068 --> 01:21:26,822
and who but a fool would do that?

908
01:21:28,228 --> 01:21:32,541
But you will be revered
and anointed as a king.

909
01:21:36,950 --> 01:21:38,509
[groans]

910
01:21:40,509 --> 01:21:43,946
You will undergo death and rebirth,

911
01:21:44,108 --> 01:21:46,067
resurrection, if you like.

912
01:21:47,108 --> 01:21:49,464
The rebirth, sadly, will not be yours,

913
01:21:49,589 --> 01:21:51,978
but that of our crops.

914
01:21:52,108 --> 01:21:55,147
I am a Christian,

915
01:21:55,269 --> 01:21:58,183
and as a Christian,
I hope for resurrection.

916
01:22:00,068 --> 01:22:02,789
And even if you kill me now,

917
01:22:02,910 --> 01:22:07,983
it is I who will live again,
not your damned apples.

918
01:22:32,549 --> 01:22:35,906
[women humming]

919
01:23:08,670 --> 01:23:13,505
♪ Sleep

920
01:23:13,630 --> 01:23:19,022
♪ Close and fast ♪

921
01:23:24,469 --> 01:23:27,268
No matter what you do,

922
01:23:27,389 --> 01:23:30,223
you can't change the fact

923
01:23:30,349 --> 01:23:32,660
that I believe in the life eternal,

924
01:23:32,790 --> 01:23:35,384
as promised to us
by Our Lord, Jesus Christ.

925
01:23:36,630 --> 01:23:39,541
♪ believe in the life eternal

926
01:23:39,670 --> 01:23:42,661
as promised to us
by Our Lord, Jesus Christ!

927
01:23:42,790 --> 01:23:44,383
[echoes resound]

928
01:23:44,509 --> 01:23:48,026
That is good,
for believing what you do,

929
01:23:48,188 --> 01:23:53,309
we confer upon you
a rare gift these days,

930
01:23:53,429 --> 01:23:55,580
a martyr's death.

931
01:23:55,710 --> 01:23:58,987
You will not only have life eternal,

932
01:23:59,108 --> 01:24:02,625
but you will sit with the saints
among the elect.

933
01:24:03,870 --> 01:24:05,098
Come.

934
01:24:06,549 --> 01:24:09,861
It is time to keep your appointment
with The Wicker Man.

935
01:24:11,029 --> 01:24:12,827
Now, wait!

936
01:24:14,349 --> 01:24:17,103
Now, all of you,
just wait and listen to me.

937
01:24:17,228 --> 01:24:22,429
And you can wrap it up any way you like.
You are about to commit murder.

938
01:24:22,549 --> 01:24:26,782
Can you not see?
There is no sun god.

939
01:24:26,910 --> 01:24:30,617
There is no goddess of the fields.

940
01:24:30,750 --> 01:24:34,424
[all start humming]

941
01:24:34,549 --> 01:24:38,339
Your crops failed
because your strains failed.

942
01:24:39,710 --> 01:24:43,339
Fruit is not meant to be grown
on these islands. It's against nature.

943
01:24:43,469 --> 01:24:47,666
Don't you see that killing me is not
going to bring back your apples?

944
01:24:48,790 --> 01:24:51,589
Summerisle, you know it won't.

945
01:24:51,710 --> 01:24:54,621
Go on, man.
Tell them. Tell them it won't!

946
01:24:54,750 --> 01:24:56,548
I know it will.

947
01:24:57,910 --> 01:25:01,790
Well, don't you understand that
if your crops fail this year,

948
01:25:01,910 --> 01:25:05,665
next year you're going to have
to have another blood sacrifice?

949
01:25:05,790 --> 01:25:09,670
And next year, no one less than
the king of Summerisle himself will do.

950
01:25:09,790 --> 01:25:11,906
If the crops fail, Summerisle,

951
01:25:12,068 --> 01:25:16,779
next year your people will kill you
on May Day.

952
01:25:16,950 --> 01:25:19,669
They will not fail.

953
01:25:19,790 --> 01:25:26,023
The sacrifice of the willing king,
like virgin fool, will be accepted.

954
01:25:26,148 --> 01:25:29,460
But don't you see, I'll be missed?
They'll come looking for me!

955
01:25:29,589 --> 01:25:32,228
There will be no traces.
Bring him up, Oak.

956
01:25:32,349 --> 01:25:34,737
- Go on.
- No! No!

957
01:25:34,870 --> 01:25:37,827
Think! Just think what you're doing!

958
01:25:37,950 --> 01:25:41,067
Think what you're doing! Think!

959
01:25:41,790 --> 01:25:44,349
In the name of God,
think what you're doing!

960
01:25:44,469 --> 01:25:46,300
[echoes resound]

961
01:25:52,549 --> 01:25:55,188
[drums beating]

962
01:26:05,549 --> 01:26:08,826
Oh, God! Oh, Jesus Christ!

963
01:26:13,068 --> 01:26:17,348
Oh, my God! Christ!

964
01:26:18,148 --> 01:26:21,779
No, no, dear God!
No, Christ!

965
01:26:34,389 --> 01:26:36,460
[geese clucking]

966
01:27:02,790 --> 01:27:05,429
[animals bleating and braying]

967
01:27:19,589 --> 01:27:21,818
No! No!

968
01:27:29,630 --> 01:27:35,103
Mighty god of the sun,
bountiful goddess of our orchards,

969
01:27:35,228 --> 01:27:40,509
accept our sacrifice
and make our blossoms fruit.

970
01:27:40,630 --> 01:27:45,260
[all] Mighty god of the sun,
bountiful goddess of our orchards...

971
01:27:45,429 --> 01:27:48,148
Hear ye the words of the Lord!

972
01:27:48,269 --> 01:27:53,299
- [all] ...and make our blossoms fruit.
- Awake, ye heathens, and hold!

973
01:27:54,750 --> 01:27:58,822
It is the Lord who hath
laid waste your orchards!

974
01:27:58,950 --> 01:28:02,067
- It is he who hath made them bare!
- Reverence the sacrifice.

975
